writeArcinfoGrid

public void writeArcinfoGrid(org.glowa.danube.tables.FloatDataTable tab,
                             java.lang.String gridName)
write a danubia FloatDataTable 'tab' as a ArcInfo ASCII Grid the the file 'gridName'. 'gridName' is created in the modelout/text/rivernetwork directory.

readArcinfoGrid

public org.glowa.danube.tables.WaterFluxTable readArcinfoGrid(org.glowa.danube.tables.FloatDataTable tab,
                                                              java.lang.String AsciiGridName)
read a ArcInfo ASCII Grid 'AsciiGridName' and convert it to a generated danubia WaterFluxTable. The grid is searched relative to the current working directory. This WaterFluxTable is returned by readArcinfoGrid(). The passed FloatDataTable 'tab' is only used to get the area-parameters.

Parameters:
tab -
AsciiGridName -
Returns:
